{"word":"νώδυνος","slug":"νώδυνος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>νώδυνος</b></el> <el>(νώ-δῠνος, ον,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><el>νη-, ὀδύνη</el>\n<br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>= <a href='S:ἀνώδυνος'><el>ἀνώδυνος</el></a>, <a href='S:quod vide'>q. <a href='S:vide'>v.</a></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>without pain</i>, <b><a href='S:Pindar'>Pind.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:active signification'><a href='S:Active voice'>act.</a></a> <i>soothing pain, anodyne</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}